<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:54PM PDT  by NWS Pendleton</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central Union
County through 545 PM PDT...
At 454 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northeast of Granite, or 17 miles west of North Powder, moving
northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Mount Ruth.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
